    "description": "<p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >&quot;201 - The Bad Number&quot; is an interactive science fiction game-book set in a post-apocalyptic Mars. In a world where only 200 people remain, each new inhabitant may hasten the end of civilization. You step into this harsh reality and confront a pivotal event—the emergence of the &quot;bad number.&quot; Now players must make choices that will impact the future of humanity and the fate of the colony.</p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><strong>Key Features:</strong></p><ul class=\"bb_ul\"><li><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >A branching narrative where every action influences the course of events.</p></li><li><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >Immersion in an unusual dystopian world of Mars, where each decision will resonate throughout the entire history of humanity.</p></li><li><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >A deep storyline with philosophical themes about time, the multiverse, and fate.</p></li><li><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >Simple controls for engaging storytelling and complex decision-making.</p></li></ul><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><i>Note: The translation of the game was done using a neural network, so there may be errors.</i></p>",
